<p class="posted"><strong>Posted by <a href="mailto&#58;quescient_nospam&#64;yahoo&#46;com">Quesci</a> at September  7, 2004 03:01 PM</strong></p>
<p>High end focus effects were changed on Lucy to affect spells above level 65 without losing effectiveness.  Time foci now work normally on spells up to level 67.  Discordant (from Muramite armor) works on spells up to level 68.  I also heard that the reduction in effectiveness was changed to 5% per level, down from 10%.  I have no way to verify that, as I can't interpret that deep in the spell data.</p>

<p>Still, the bump is heartening for those of us who burned a lot of DKP on GoD items only to learn that they were going to be useless.  Now, my 45% damage focus will work on spells up to level 68, and even level 70 spells will receive 40.5%.</p>

<p>For those who will say "But what about those of us without access to Time/GoD focuses?" -- well, the same thing happened when poP came out, but worse.  Those of us without VT access saw our focuses become totally useless.  I used level 60 spells for ages after PoP came out because I didn't have the focuses.   At least this time your old focus items will still work, instead of totally conking out like they did in PoP.</p>
